<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Unique-Constraint on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/unique-constraint/</link><description>Recent content in Unique-Constraint on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/unique-constraint/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] SQL Duplicate Entry Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/duplicate-entry/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/duplicate-entry/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="sql-duplicate-entry-error-fix"&gt;SQL Duplicate Entry Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when an INSERT or UPDATE tries to store a duplicate value in a column with a UNIQUE or PRIMARY KEY constraint. The message reads: &lt;code&gt;Duplicate entry 'X' for key 'Y'&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;UNIQUE constraints enforce that every value in a column (or combination of columns) is distinct. Attempting to insert or update a row with a value that already exists violates this rule and raises an error.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] SQL Duplicate Entry Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-duplicate-entry/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-duplicate-entry/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when an INSERT or UPDATE statement tries to insert a value that already exists in a column with a UNIQUE or PRIMARY KEY constraint. The message reads: &lt;code&gt;Duplicate entry 'X' for key 'Y'&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The database enforces uniqueness on certain columns. When you try to insert or update a row with a value that duplicates an existing one in a unique column, the operation is rejected.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] SQL Duplicate Entry for PRIMARY KEY Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-duplicate-entry-v2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-duplicate-entry-v2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="sql-duplicate-entry-for-primary-key-error-fix"&gt;SQL Duplicate Entry for PRIMARY KEY Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A SQL duplicate entry error occurs when you try to insert or update a row with a PRIMARY KEY or UNIQUE constraint value that already exists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The database enforces uniqueness constraints. When an INSERT or UPDATE produces a duplicate value for a PRIMARY KEY or UNIQUE column, the operation is rejected with a duplicate entry error.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inserting a record with an ID that already exists&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Race condition between check and insert&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Uploading/importing duplicate data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Not using auto-increment properly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-use-insert-ignore-or-on-duplicate-key"&gt;1. Use INSERT IGNORE or ON DUPLICATE KEY&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- CORRECT: Handle duplicates gracefully
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;INSERT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;IGNORE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;INTO&lt;/span&gt; users (id, name, email)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;VALUES&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Alice&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;alice@example.com&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Or use ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;INSERT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;INTO&lt;/span&gt; users (id, name, email)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;VALUES&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Alice&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;alice@example.com&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ON&lt;/span&gt; DUPLICATE &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;KEY&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;UPDATE&lt;/span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;VALUES&lt;/span&gt;(name);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="2-check-before-inserting"&gt;2. Check before inserting&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- CORRECT: Verify existence first
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; users &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;WHERE&lt;/span&gt; id &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- If 0, insert; otherwise update
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="3-use-replace-mysql"&gt;3. Use REPLACE (MySQL)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- CORRECT: Replace existing record
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;REPLACE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;INTO&lt;/span&gt; users (id, name, email)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;VALUES&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Alice Updated&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;alice@example.com&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="4-use-upsert-pattern"&gt;4. Use UPSERT pattern&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- CORRECT: PostgreSQL upsert
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;INSERT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;INTO&lt;/span&gt; users (id, name, email)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;VALUES&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Alice&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;alice@example.com&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ON&lt;/span&gt; CONFLICT (id)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DO&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;UPDATE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SET&lt;/span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; EXCLUDED.name, email &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; EXCLUDED.email;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="sql-foreign-key-v2"&gt;SQL Foreign Key&lt;/a&gt; — constraint violations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="sql-data-truncated-v2"&gt;SQL Data Truncated&lt;/a&gt; — data type issues&lt;/li&gt;
